text: Celal is both a masculine Turkish given name and a surname. It is the Turkish form of the Arabic word Jalal (جلال), which means "majesty". Notable people with the name include: Given name: * Celal Atik (1918–1979), Turkish sports wrestler * Celâl Bayar (1883–1986), Turkish politician * Celal Kandemiroglu (born 1953), video game specialist * Celal Şahin (1925–2018), Turkish musician and humorist * Celâl Şengör (born 1955), Turkish geologist * Hasan Celal Güzel (born 1945), Turkish politician Surname: * Peride Celal (1916-2013), Turkish female novelist, story writer Category:Turkish-language surnames Category:Turkish masculine given names
title: Celal
